article.headline: Presbyterian 72, Radford 64
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Al'Lonzo Coleman had 19 points and 13 rebounds, and Presbyterian held off Radford 72-64 on Saturday night. Khalid Mutakabbir added 15 points, Jay Reynolds had 14 and Pierre Miller 10 for the Blue Hose (4-4, 1-1 Big South Conference), who snapped a two-game losing streak. Free-throw shooting made the difference as Presbyterian made 23 of 32 from the line, including 14 of 16 in the final 6 minutes. Radford made 7 of 11. The Highlanders (3-6, 0-2) fell behind by 13 points in the first half but went on a 10-2 run over the final 3:08 to trim the deficit to 32-27 at halftime. Presbyterian opened the second half on an 8-1 run and kept the lead in double digits until the final minutes. Johnathan Edwards tied his career high with 16 points, Blake Smith added 15 and Javonte Green 14 for the Highlanders, who lost their fifth straight.
